<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: expression_extensions_schema  Entity: literal_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="expression_extensions_schema::expression_extensions_schema.literal_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="expression_extensions_schema.literal_assignment">
The literal_assignment entity relates a literal value to an expression subject to the context of an entity instance.
<example> The factual statement that "the power of airplane 123456 is ON" can be represented by a logical_expression "POWERON" having a logical_literal value of "TRUE" with respect to the entity_instance with "the_entity" pointing to an entity_expression with "name" equal to "AIRPLANE" and the_instance attribute pointing to, hypothetically, an "AIRPLANE" entity instance with airplane_id = 123456.
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: expression_extensions_schema  Entity: literal_assignment  Attribute: base 
   <express_ref linkend="expression_extensions_schema::expression_extensions_schema.literal_assignment.base"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="expression_extensions_schema.literal_assignment.base">
	the expression for which the literal value represents.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
