<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: expression_extensions_schema  Entity: variable_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="expression_extensions_schema::expression_extensions_schema.variable_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="expression_extensions_schema.variable_assignment">
The variable_assignment is a binding of a variable to a defined_function.
<note>The generic_binary_expression could conceptually fulfill this role. However the semantics is not clear and can cause potential confusions and mistakes.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: expression_extensions_schema  Entity: variable_assignment  Attribute: the_function 
   <express_ref linkend="expression_extensions_schema::expression_extensions_schema.variable_assignment.the_function"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="expression_extensions_schema.variable_assignment.the_function">the function to which a variable is assigned.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: expression_extensions_schema  Entity: variable_assignment  Attribute: the_variable 
   <express_ref linkend="expression_extensions_schema::expression_extensions_schema.variable_assignment.the_variable"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="expression_extensions_schema.variable_assignment.the_variable">the variable assigned to a function.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: expression_extensions_schema  Entity: variable_entity_type  
   <express_ref linkend="expression_extensions_schema::expression_extensions_schema.variable_entity_type"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="expression_extensions_schema.variable_entity_type">A variable whose range is an entity in an  ISO 10303 schema. It is assumed that the identified entity type belongs to the same schema as the application using the variable.
</ext_description>
